  1→# Nurge Dashboard — Implementation Plan
  2→
  3→**Goal:** Build the dashboard at `app.nurge.sh` — handles Google OAuth login for the nurge CLI and provides a minimal account page.
  4→
  5→**Tech Stack:** Next.js 15 (App Router), Convex, Convex Auth, Google OAuth, Tailwind CSS, Vercel
  6→
  7→**Spec:** `docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-22-nurge-account-auth-design.md`
  8→
  9→---
 10→
 11→## What the dashboard does
 12→
 13→The CLI (`nurge init`) opens the browser to `app.nurge.sh/cli-auth?port=PORT&state=STATE`. The dashboard:
 14→
 15→1. Shows "Sign in with Google"
 16→2. After auth, creates a one-time code in Convex
 17→3. Redirects to `localhost:PORT/callback?code=CODE&state=STATE`
 18→4. CLI exchanges the code for an API token via Convex HTTP action
 19→
 20→The dashboard also exposes 3 HTTP action endpoints the CLI calls directly:
 21→- `POST /api/validate-token` — check if a token is valid
 22→- `POST /api/exchange-code` — swap auth code for API token
 23→- `POST /api/revoke-token` — delete a token (logout)
 24→
 25→---
 26→
 27→## Task 1: Scaffold the project
 28→
 29→```bash
 30→cd /Users/rejoesudarsan/Projects
 31→mkdir nurge-dashboard && cd nurge-dashboard
 32→
 33→# Next.js
 34→npx create-next-app@latest . --typescript --tailwind --app --src-dir --eslint --no-import-alias
 35→
 36→# Convex
 37→npx convex dev --once
 38→# Follow prompts — name it "nurge-dashboard"
 39→
 40→# Convex Auth
 41→npm install @convex-dev/auth @auth/core@0.37.0
 42→npx @convex-dev/auth
 43→# This scaffolds auth files and generates JWT keys
 44→
 45→# Git
 46→git init
 47→git add .
 48→git commit -m "feat: scaffold Next.js + Convex project"
 49→```
 50→
 51→---
 52→
 53→## Task 2: Schema
 54→
 55→Write `convex/schema.ts`:
 56→
 57→```typescript
 58→import { defineSchema, defineTable } from "convex/server";
 59→import { authTables } from "@convex-dev/auth/server";
 60→import { v } from "convex/values";
 61→
 62→export default defineSchema({
 63→  ...authTables,
 64→
 65→  apiTokens: defineTable({
 66→    userId: v.id("users"),
 67→    token: v.string(),
 68→    deviceName: v.optional(v.string()),
 69→    createdAt: v.number(),
 70→    lastUsedAt: v.number(),
 71→    expiresAt: v.optional(v.number()),
 72→  })
 73→    .index("by_token", ["token"])
 74→    .index("by_userId", ["userId"]),
 75→
 76→  authCodes: defineTable({
 77→    code: v.string(),
 78→    userId: v.id("users"),
 79→    expiresAt: v.number(),
 80→    used: v.boolean(),
 81→  }).index("by_code", ["code"]),
 82→});
 83→```
 84→
 85→`authTables` gives you the `users` table. You only add `apiTokens` (CLI tokens) and `authCodes` (one-time codes for the CLI handshake).
 86→
 87→```bash
 88→npx convex dev --once
 89→git add convex/schema.ts
 90→git commit -m "feat: add apiTokens and authCodes schema"
 91→```
